<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5fff70d6-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s302"><num value="302">§ 302.</num><heading> Assignment of lease; subletting</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The right conferred by this chapter may, subject to the approval of the Secretary of the Interior, be assigned or sublet by the owner thereof to any corporation, firm, association, or individual.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id5fff70d7-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/act/1930-05-21/ch307/s2">May 21, 1930, ch. 307, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/46/373">46 Stat. 373</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
